You can use CSS selectors to style specific elements by targeting their HTML tag, class or ID. 

HTML tag: 
To style all elements of a particular HTML tag, add the tag name before the CSS selector, such as:

```
h1 {
  color: blue;
}
```

Class: 
To style all elements with a particular class, add a dot before the class name, such as:

```
.my-class {
  font-size: 16px;
}
```

ID: 
To style only one element with a particular ID, add a hash (#) before the ID name, such as:

```
#my-element {
  background-color: yellow;
}
```

Combination: You can also combine CSS selectors to create more specific rules. For example:

```
.header h1 {
  color: red;
}
```
This targets only the h1 elements within the HTML class 'header'.

